title: Graylog: Sidecars
agents: graylog
catalog: app/graylog
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 With this check you can monitor sidecars of a Graylog instance. It outputs the
 state of the sidecar, when the sidecar was last seen and the state of the
 collectors of the sidecar. Collector details can be found in the long output of
 the service. You can choose if the service is shown on the queried graylog
 host or the sidecar host.

 Needs the datasource "Check state of Graylog" to be configured.

item:
 The item is the name of the sidecar.

inventory:
 One service for each node {"Graylog Sidecar my_sidecar"} will be created.
